"Poured on tap in a shaker pint, the beer is a cloudy, muddled, opaque, caramel brown coloring with no head. Aromas of apple, candi sugar, toffee, dates, fig, and a spice blend of cinnamon, nutmeg, and clove. Flavors are roasted and sweet forward, with apple, subtle creme, tangy toffee, cinnamon, nutmeg, and clove. A wee bit off-balanced. The body is robust and boozy, with a candy apple aftertaste. Rich, slick finish with a building warmth."
""
