"Candied dates, raisins, deeply caramelized malt, toasted bread, and light floral notes counter a touch of dark cherry in aroma. Flavor reveals a fairly sweet, buttery, nutty toffee start, which becomes dry and toasted mid palate, anchored by a cherry character reminiscent of the aftertaste of cough syrup.  Wish the medicinal finish weren't quite so pronounced. Incredible aroma. Finish is more dry than I'd prefer, but I guess that's the Brett, as I just read the description."
