"Poured into a snifter.  Brown in color; lighter around the edges when held up to light.  Some head with little lace.  The nose is all over the place, with stronger notes of vanilla, dark fruit (with some apple and pear) and cocoa taking control here.  The taste follows suit.  Really intense and layered, with so much malty depth.  Unpretentious despite its complexity.  A big beer at 10% ABV, but not overly boozy.  Seriously, this is one fine beer.  A commendable effort from the fine folks who made this possible.  Cheers."
""
""
""
"Note: When my wife and I first tasted this beer, it was fridge cold.  Our fault for being thirsty and impatient.  The beer presents a strong metallic/penny/blood flavor when cold, to the point of seeming decidedly off-flavor, but this fades and is completely gone by the time it gets to the recommended temperature.  Many beers served colder than recommended only sacrifice peak flavor.  In my experience this is a less common one, one that will be downright off, even to the point where you may be tempted to write off the beer. So let this one sit on the counter for a good 20-25 minutes if pulling from a conventional refrigerator. You will not regret it."
"I'd prefer to revisit this in about 3-4 years minimum, but alas, I doubt there's a drop of this beer outside of Anodyne's keg."
